abstract: Bureau of Economic Analysis inadvertently releases data early indicating United States consumer spending rose 0.3 percent in November, to $12.43 trillion, from revised $12.39 trillion in October.
lead_paragraph: United States consumer spending rose in November by 0.3 percent, according to official data inadvertently released about 12 hours ahead of schedule.

headline.main: Early Release of Data Shows 0.3% Rise in Consumer Spending
headline.print_headline: Early Release of Data Shows a Rise in Consumer Spending
